  "texts": [
    "The majority of these parameters of lung function was not significantly correlated with PM 2.5, and only PEF and PEF 25 were significantly correlated with PM 2.5 exposure concentrations at lag 0-1 week (Table 2).",
    "Overall, the majority of the parameters related to lung function was significantly decreased in response to PM 2.5 exposure concentration at lag 1 week in the control group.",
    "However, weaker associations with no statistical significance were observed in the Qiju group.",
    "Lung function did not vary significantly at lag 0 week and 0-1 week in response to PM 2.5 exposures in either group (Figures 3, 4).",
    "As shown in Figure 3, FEV 1 and PEF, which are the major parameters of large airway function, were negatively correlated with PM 2.5 exposure concentrations in the control group at lag 1 week, but not statistically significant in the Qiju group."
